ST. Paul, MINI. The City
Council has adopted a new civil
rights ordinance banning dis
elimination in public accommo-
dations, housing, public services
and education.


The ordinance adopted ON Aug.
20. also established a special
ll-man commission to investi-
gate charges Of violations and to
enforce the new law. Enforce
ment will include fines and work
house terms for violators Of the
employment ban and various other
sanctions in other areas.


Prior to the new ordinance,

employment practices measure.
